# Modern CSS Practices

When writing or refactoring CSS in this project, prefer patterns from **modern-css.com**. Full reference: **markdowns/MODERN-CSS-PRACTICES.md**.

## Quick preferences

- **Layout:** Use `display: grid; place-items: center` for centering (not transform hack). Use `gap` instead of margin hacks. Use `aspect-ratio` instead of padding hack. Use `inset: 0` instead of top/right/bottom/left. Use `100dvh` for full-height on mobile.
- **Selectors:** Use `:focus-visible` for focus styles (not `:focus`). Use `:is()` or `:where()` to group selectors. Use `:has()` for parent selection when appropriate.
- **Colors/theme:** Use CSS custom properties (we have colors.css). Prefer `color-mix()` or `light-dark()` over duplicating light/dark values where supported.
- **Motion:** Always respect `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` when adding animations.
- **Forms:** Prefer `accent-color` for checkbox/radio; `field-sizing: content` for auto-growing textarea; `:user-invalid` / `:user-valid` where it fits.

Do not rewrite existing CSS gratuitously; apply these when touching the same area or adding new styles.
